# opencode-mcp-adapter

OpenCode plugin that wraps MCP servers as native tools. This allows MCP tools to go through the `tool.definition` hook, making them compatible with tool-search and other plugins.

## Problem

MCP tools in OpenCode bypass the `tool.definition` hook, so plugins like `opencode-tool-search` can't defer their descriptions.

## Solution

This plugin:
1. Connects to MCP servers defined in plugin config (not opencode.jsonc's mcp section)
2. Fetches tools from each MCP server
3. Wraps them as native plugin tools (1:1 mapping)
4. These tools go through `tool.definition` hook and can be deferred

## Usage

### Install

```bash
npm install opencode-mcp-adapter @modelcontextprotocol/sdk
```

### Configure

Add to `~/.config/opencode/opencode.jsonc`:

```jsonc
{
  "plugin": [
    ["opencode-mcp-adapter", {
      "servers": [
        {
          "name": "github",
          "type": "local",
          "command": ["npx", "-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-github"],
          "env": {
            "GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN": "your-token"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "filesystem",
          "type": "local",
          "command": ["npx", "-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem", "/path/to/files"]
        },
        {
          "name": "remote-server",
          "type": "remote",
          "url": "https://example.com/mcp"
        }
      ]
    }]
  ]
}
```

### Use with tool-search

```jsonc
{
  "plugin": [
    ["opencode-tool-search", {
      "alwaysLoad": ["read", "write", "bash"]
    }],
    ["opencode-mcp-adapter", {
      "servers": [
        {
          "name": "github",
          "type": "local",
          "command": ["npx", "-y", "@modelcontextprotocol/server-github"]
        }
      ]
    }]
  ]
}
```

Now MCP tools (e.g., `github_create_issue`) will be deferred by tool-search!

